
Settings
========

 * Normal Django settings
 * Normal django-cms2 settings
 * widget overrides::

     CMS_ADMIN_WIDGETS = lambda: __import__('semanticeditor.widgets', {}, {}, ['widgets']).__dict__


Templates
=========
Automatically found if 'django.template.loaders.app_directories.load_template_source'
is in TEMPLATE_LOADERS.

Media
=====
media files: media/semanticeditor needs to be copied/linked/served so that it is
under MEDIA_URL.  (i.e. side-by-side with the media/cms directory).  Then::

  SE_MEDIA_URL = os.path.join(MEDIA_URL, "semanticeditor/")


URLS
====
Add the following to the root URL conf::

  (r'^semantic/', include('semanticeditor.urls')),

These are needed for views

Models
======
Install the models
::

  ./manage.py syncdb


Usage
=====

Use 'SemanticEditor' as the widget in {% placeholder %} tags instead of
'WYMEditor' or 'Textarea'
